CatDescriptText: Ida Mae Horsley, 4740 Sylvan Avenue was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, August 23, 1958, pg. A1 with question: "In the coming November elections, do you think voters should elect another Democratic Governor or change to a Republican?" answer reads: "I think there should be another Democratic Governor. Their candidate, Mayor Lawrence, has done a lot of good for the community and therefore will do a lot of good for the state."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Ida Mae Horsley, wearing eyeglasses, and sleeveless dress with polka dot trim and straps, standing on sidewalk of street, with automobiles, billboards, and buildings in background, hand holding spiral note tablet on center left margin
